    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1895-12-07T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1895-12-07T00:00:00-05:00" n="434"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d434">
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Olney</persName> to Mr. <persName
                            type="to">Runyon</persName>
                    </hi>.</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>,<lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1895-12-07">
                            <hi rend="italic">December 7, 1895</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                    <seg rendition="#left">No. 490.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: Referring to a letter of this date, inclosing a
                    communication from the governor of the State of New York, together with copies
                    of communications from the superintendent of insurance of the State of Missouri,
                    I send you herewith copy of letter to this Department from superintendent of
                    insurance of the State of New York, from which it <pb facs="0509" n="449"
                        xml:id="pg_449"/> appears that he has requested Mr. Poultney Bigelow to act
                    as his representative with the proper officers of the Kingdom of Prussia in
                    reference to the subject-matter of his letter.</p>
                <p>Please do anything in your power to facilitate the objects of Mr. Bigelow’s
                    mission, by giving him access to the proper Prussian officials or otherwise.</p>
                <p>Respectfully, yours,</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Richard Olney</hi>
                    </signed>.</closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
